{
  "number": 1899,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/1899",
  "title": "Is it possible to search multiple attributes or merge two attributes?",
  "body": "Bit of a confusing one so hopefully it makes sense. \r\n\r\nWe have two attributes that need searching from one select dropdown (custom widget built by @vvo). These are modelSimple and selectVehicle.modelSimple. The way the index is set up, we need to use one dropdown to search values within both. Is this possible? The widget only has 'attributeName', not 'attributes'.\r\n\r\nOne theory is to get the value of a toggle in jQuery and then show / hide separate fields. Doing it this way we query whether or not the toggle item is active (hasClass). This triggers twice and doesn't appear to be reliable so we've reached a bit of a hurdle that we're working on.\r\n\r\nDoes anybody know if this is possible? Or which is the best approach for something like this?\r\n\r\nThanks!\r\n\r\n",
